title: Fuel leaking near explosives factory
text:
Bruce Highway blocked, 200L of fuel leaking outside explosives factory Melanie Plane, News Corp Australia February 15, 2017 11:07am 
A VEHICLE carrying 200 litres of fuel has rolled on the Bruce Hwy about 30km south of Rockhampton outside the Bajool explosives factory. 
The Gladstone Observer understands a dual-cab vehicle was carrying a 200L tank of diesel when it hit the side of a bridge and the fuel is now leaking onto the road. 
The two occupants of the vehicle are out of the vehicle and are being assessed at the scene. 
It is understood two lanes of the Hwy is blocked at this stage. 
A Bajool community member has confirmed traffic is backing up on the Bruce Hwy.
